 .TH RON 1 "February 2026" "Ron Bot v2.0.0" "User Commands"
 .SH NAME
 ron \- friendly Discord bot focused on wellness and moderation utilities

 .SH SYNOPSIS
 .B ron-start
 .br
 .B ron-stop
 .br
 .B ron-status

 .SH DESCRIPTION
 Ron is a friendly Discord bot providing wellness reminders, motivational features, and moderation utilities designed to help communities stay healthy, hydrated, and organized.

 The bot connects to Discord and responds to both prefix commands (default: \fB!\fR) and slash commands (\fB/\fR).

 .SH COMMANDS

 .SS Moderation & Management
 .TP
 .B /purge \fICOUNT\fR
 Bulk-delete the most recent messages in the current channel. Moderators only. Count must be between 1 and 100.

 .TP
 .B /announce \fICHANNEL MESSAGE\fR
 Post a highlighted announcement embed into the specified channel. Moderators only.

 .SS Fun & Games
 .TP
 .B /ping
 Check bot latency and response time in milliseconds.

 .TP
 .B /roll \fINdM\fR
 Roll dice using NdM format (N = number of dice, M = sides per die). Supports up to 100 dice.

 .TP
 .B /quote
 Send a random motivational quote from the built-in collection.

 .SS Wellness & Health
 .TP
 .B /waterreminder
 Subscribe or unsubscribe from hourly hydration reminders. The bot will send hourly DM reminders with a rotating set of encouraging phrases.

 .TP
 .B /workout
 Get a random quick workout suggestion â€” short circuits and micro-workouts for breaks.

 .TP
 .B /breathing
 Guided breathing exercises to reduce stress and improve focus.

 .TP
 .B /tip
 Get a daily wellness tip covering sleep, nutrition, movement, and mindfulness.

 .TP
 .B /motivate
 Quick motivational affirmation boost.

 .SS Reminders
 .TP
 .B /remind \fIMINUTES MESSAGE\fR
 Set a personal DM reminder that will be sent after the specified number of minutes.

 Examples:
   \fB/remind 10 Take a break\fR
   \fB!remind 30 Drink water and stretch\fR

 .SS Information & Management
 .TP
 .B /help
 Show all available commands with descriptions and usage examples.

 .TP
 .B /about
 Display information about Ron Bot, its features, and available commands.

 .TP
 .B !sync
 Manually synchronize slash commands with Discord. Owner-only.

 .SH INSTALLATION

 .SS Quick Install
 .nf
 cd /path/to/Ron-Bot
 ./scripts/install.sh
 .fi

 .SS Manual Install
 .nf
 python3 -m venv .venv
 source .venv/bin/activate
 pip install -r requirements.txt
 cp .env.example .env
 # Edit .env with your DISCORD_TOKEN
 python3 scripts/ron_bot.py
 .fi

 .SH USAGE

 .SS Starting the Bot
 .nf
 ron-start              # Using symlink (if installed)
 ./scripts/run_ron.sh   # Direct script
 .fi

 .SS Stopping the Bot
 .nf
 ron-stop               # Using symlink
 ./scripts/stop_ron.sh  # Direct script
 .fi

 .SS Checking Status
 .nf
 ron-status             # Using symlink
 ./scripts/ron-status.sh # Direct script
 .fi

 .SS Viewing Logs
 .nf
 tail -f ron.log              # Real-time log
 tail -50 ron.log             # Last 50 lines
 grep ERROR ron.log           # Errors only
 .fi

 .SH CONFIGURATION

 .SS Environment Variables
 Required in \fB.env\fR file:

 .TP
 .B DISCORD_TOKEN
 Your Discord bot token from the Developer Portal. Required for bot operation.

 .TP
 .B PREFIX
 Command prefix (default: \fB!\fR). Change to customize prefix for your server.

